Date: Fri, 10 Jan 2025 09:35:11 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/1] vsock: prevent null-ptr-deref in
 vsock_*[has_data|has_space]
Git-commit: 91751e248256efc111e52e15115840c35d85abaf
Patch-mainline: v6.13
References: CVE-2025-21666 bsc#1236680

Recent reports have shown how we sometimes call vsock_*_has_data()
when a vsock socket has been de-assigned from a transport (see attached
links), but we shouldn't.

Previous commits should have solved the real problems, but we may have
more in the future, so to avoid null-ptr-deref, we can return 0
(no space, no data available) but with a warning.

This way the code should continue to run in a nearly consistent state
and have a warning that allows us to debug future problems.

Fixes: c0cfa2d8a788 ("vsock: add multi-transports support")
